{"mem_mpd9m3lc_892383fa8f65":{"concepts":["VEX","Expo SDK 54","TypeScript strict","React Navigation","Supabase","TanStack Query","Zustand","Zod"],"content":"VEX is a production Expo React Native app in C:/Users/jonat/CascadeProjects/vex-app-old. Stack policy: Expo SDK 54 managed workflow, TypeScript strict/noImplicitAny/strictNullChecks/noUncheckedIndexedAccess, TanStack Query v5 for server state only, Zustand for persistent client state only, Zod schemas as source of truth with z.infer types, React Navigation v6 fully typed, Reanimated 3 only, Supabase Postgres/Auth/Realtime/Storage, MMKV for non-sensitive storage, SecureStore only through existing wrapper for secrets, Sentry for unexpected errors, RevenueCat only through shared monetization layer, and design tokens from src/theme/tokens. No new libraries without explicit user instruction.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.414Z","files":["AGENTS.md","package.json","src_impl"],"id":"mem_mpd9m3lc_892383fa8f65","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"VEX is a production Expo React Native app in C:/Users/jonat/CascadeProjects/vex-","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.414Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m3ly_b6fd26f32a4f":{"concepts":["VEX architecture","feature layout","data flow","repository service hooks components"],"content":"VEX feature architecture is mandatory: each feature belongs in features/<name>/ with types.ts, schemas.ts, repository.ts, service.ts, hooks.ts, optional store.ts, events.ts, analytics.ts, components/, and __tests__. Data flow must be Component -> Hook -> Service -> Repository -> Supabase. Supabase queries are only allowed in repository.ts. Business logic/calculations belong in service.ts. Components render UI only. useQuery/useMutation must be wrapped in hooks.ts, not called directly in components.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.435Z","files":["AGENTS.md","src_impl/features","src/features"],"id":"mem_mpd9m3ly_b6fd26f32a4f","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"VEX feature architecture is mandatory: each feature belongs in features/<name>/ ","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.435Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m3m5_992c91cc998a":{"concepts":["VEX banned patterns","file size","typescript zero tolerance"],"content":"VEX hard rules: every file must stay under 200 lines. No any/as any/z.any, no @ts-ignore/@ts-nocheck, no console.log, no TODO in shipped code, no Animated from react-native, no StyleSheet.create, no FlatList (use FlashList with accurate estimatedItemSize), no AsyncStorage, no raw fetch, no hardcoded colors/spacing/font/radius, no Supabase outside repositories, no stubs or fake happy-path-only implementations. All async functions need explicit return types and typed catch handling.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.453Z","files":["AGENTS.md","TASKSxxxx.md"],"id":"mem_mpd9m3m5_992c91cc998a","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"VEX hard rules: every file must stay under 200 lines. No any/as any/z.any, no @t","type":"preference","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.453Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m3mc_d13651f32c2e":{"concepts":["VEX source of truth","TASKSxxxx","launch plan","May 30 2026"],"content":"Current launch source of truth is TASKSxxxx.md, not older TASKSxx/TASKSxxx archive docs unless explicitly requested. Target App Store submission is May 30, 2026. Launch promise: Open VEX -> see one thing that matters -> start focus fast -> finish -> feel seen by companion -> know what tomorrow is for. A checkbox is not complete until proof is recorded in VERIFICATION_REPORT.md. Main product loop prioritizes one primary action, companion memory, premium session completion, Day Two retention, honest monetization, offline trust, accessibility, and App Store readiness.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.453Z","files":["TASKSxxxx.md","VERIFICATION_REPORT.md"],"id":"mem_mpd9m3mc_d13651f32c2e","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Current launch source of truth is TASKSxxxx.md, not older TASKSxx/TASKSxxx archi","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.453Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m3mz_cb6cc0a29c40":{"concepts":["VEX UI states","accessibility","offline","optimistic","verification"],"content":"Every VEX data-driven component must ship loading skeleton, error state using ErrorState where applicable, empty state with VEX voice and one CTA, success state, offline degraded banner via useNetInfo, and optimistic UI for important writes. Interactive elements require accessibilityLabel, accessibilityRole, accessibilityHint and 44x44 minimum touch target via touchTarget utility. Haptics must go through src/utils/haptics.ts named functions only. Reanimated animations must respect reduced motion.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.453Z","files":["AGENTS.md","src_impl/components/states","src_impl/network","src_impl/utils/touchTarget.ts","src_impl/utils/haptics.ts"],"id":"mem_mpd9m3mz_cb6cc0a29c40","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Every VEX data-driven component must ship loading skeleton, error state using Er","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.453Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m3nw_b63ad96921f1":{"concepts":["VEX project structure","src_impl","src mirrors","features","navigation","theme"],"content":"VEX has both src and src_impl. TASKSxxxx says edit real implementation files in src_impl, not mirrored shells in src, unless the app root requires it. src_impl contains navigation, screens, features, theme tokens, API, analytics, validation, Supabase types, and tests. src/types/navigation.ts re-exports src_impl/types/navigation.ts. Theme tokens live in src_impl/theme/tokens and src/theme/tokens with colors, spacing, typography, radius, shadows, sizing, timing, opacity, zIndex.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.518Z","files":["src_impl","src","src_impl/navigation","src_impl/theme/tokens"],"id":"mem_mpd9m3nw_b63ad96921f1","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"VEX has both src and src_impl. TASKSxxxx says edit real implementation files in ","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.518Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m3xi_c57740346822":{"concepts":["VEX verification","typecheck","lint","test","banned audit","file size audit"],"content":"Before declaring VEX implementation complete, run npm run typecheck -- --pretty false, npm run lint when relevant/full phase, relevant npm test commands, banned pattern audit: rg \"console\\.|: any\\b|<any>|@ts-ignore|@ts-nocheck|StyleSheet\\.create|FlatList|AsyncStorage|fetch\\(\" src_impl, and file-size audit for edited scope under 200 lines. Record evidence in VERIFICATION_REPORT.md.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.868Z","files":["package.json","VERIFICATION_REPORT.md"],"id":"mem_mpd9m3xi_c57740346822","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Before declaring VEX implementation complete, run npm run typecheck -- --pretty ","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:36.868Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m47e_9d098d08c864":{"concepts":["VEX Phase status","Supabase","RLS","blocked history"],"content":"VERIFICATION_REPORT.md records Phase 1 schema/RLS work: linked Supabase project icnbpjkyupuqzuvwuvbk had migrations applied through 202605150004, types regenerated to src_impl/types/supabase.ts, typecheck/lint/schema reconciliation tests passed, banned-pattern audit passed, and remote RLS abuse tests passed for launch-critical tables. Local Docker reset remained unavailable, but remote/staging-equivalent testing completed. Always inspect current files and latest report because newer phases may have changed this.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:37.225Z","files":["VERIFICATION_REPORT.md","supabase/migrations","src_impl/types/supabase.ts"],"id":"mem_mpd9m47e_9d098d08c864","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"VERIFICATION_REPORT.md records Phase 1 schema/RLS work: linked Supabase project ","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:37.225Z","version":1},"mem_mpd9m4ha_5675ea8c58b7":{"concepts":["memory usage","VEX","Codex"],"content":"For future VEX Codex sessions: first use codebase-memory-mcp project C-Users-jonat-CascadeProjects-vex-app-old to search architecture/definitions before broad grep, and use agentmemory recall for prior VEX decisions. Treat memory as a shortcut only; current repo files are source of truth when memory disagrees.","createdAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:37.580Z","files":["C:/Users/jonat/.codex/config.toml",".codebase-memory/graph.db.zst"],"id":"mem_mpd9m4ha_5675ea8c58b7","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"For future VEX Codex sessions: first use codebase-memory-mcp project C-Users-jon","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-19T23:29:37.580Z","version":1}}␀␀␀Ą␀␀Üĸĸ